fonts:
Four roles, BRAND.md set, NO substitutions (owner's Space Mono choice is final). PAIRING LAW: Tanker is the building, Zodiak is the person telling you about the block, Satoshi is the clerk reading the file, Space Mono is the survey record itself.
- TANKER (display/wordmark/section-mass) — condensed, heavy, chiseled; run LARGE and often uppercase; headlines ("Know the block before you knock."), big addresses, section markers. Tracking -0.01em on wordmark/headers; leading 0.9 on display. var(--pb-font-display).
- ZODIAK slab (the voice / editorial / long-form) — explainers, glossary definitions, community-signal sentences, empty states, value-derivation prose, legend captions. THIS is where warmth lives: set long-form at base15 / line-height 1.65 with a generous ~64ch measure so the teach rail reads like a margin note from a neighbor, not chrome. Weights 400/700/700i. var(--pb-font-serif).
- SATOSHI (UI/body/labels/table-cell prose/secondary buttons) — the clerk; weights 400/500 for body, 700/900 reserved for table headers and sub-heads. Never letterspaced as body. var(--pb-font-ui).
- SPACE MONO (the evidentiary layer) — ALL data + records: parcel/OPA IDs, prices, $/SF, coords, timestamps, SOURCE STAMPS, metric labels+numbers, pills, primary-button labels, ledger values, legend break ticks, the instrument readout. Mono labels uppercase +0.12em. Weights 400/700/400i. var(--pb-font-mono).
EXACT IMPORTS (two lines, keep separate; already verified in repo TOKENS.css lines 8-9):
@import url("https://api.fontshare.com/v2/css?f[]=tanker@400&f[]=zodiak@700,400,700i&f[]=satoshi@900,700,500,400&display=swap");
@import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Mono:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&display=swap");
SELF-HOST (ship for AGPL, no hard CDN dependency): repo _fonts/ carries woff2 + @font-face for each (tanker.css, zodiak.css, satoshi.css, spacemono.css, plus embedded.css). Stacks: --pb-font-display:"Tanker",system-ui,sans-serif; --pb-font-serif:"Zodiak",Georgia,serif; --pb-font-ui:"Satoshi",system-ui,-apple-system,sans-serif; --pb-font-mono:"Space Mono",ui-monospace,monospace.
TYPE SCALE (px, BRAND.md): xs11 / sm13 / base15 / lg18 / xl22 / 2xl30 / 3xl44 / 4xl62, PLUS one brutalist-forward display step --pb-text-5xl 84px (Tanker hero ONLY — the one place mass goes all the way up). prefers-reduced-motion does not affect type.
